Dug back through the PO club archives, and this thread was still there. I brought the following up, using some quotes from G.Dyson's book which quoted Taylor recently.<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
My message <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/projectorion/message/12224">12224</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> said<br>
<br>
in #12201 Yale wrote:<br>
&gt; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I would think that -based on Ted's views on bombs, and<br>
his hopes for Orion (which was a MEANS to explore space)<br>
the statement: (Dyson)&quot;Ted’s hope is that the dream of<br>
Orion will one day be disentangled from the nightmare of<br>
the bomb.&quot; may be best read as his hope to EXPLORE, not<br>
to build an atomic bomb powered rocket.<br>
 The fact that he has devoted much effort to non-atomic<br>
space travel technologies to further that goal reinforced<br>
that interpretation.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
If you read the entire quote, you get a different impression:<br>
Message 12198 by brp13 (from Dyson's book)<br>
“ <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> We haven’t opened Pandora’s box and found the really<br>
important content of that box which was hope. Down in the<br>
bottom. If we just fiddle around at the surface, all kinds of<br>
terrible things come out. We just freeze up and say, ‘No, no,<br>
no, no. That can’t be done. Not allowable.’<br>
” Ted’s hope is that the dream of Orion will one day be<br>
disentangled from the nightmare of the bomb.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
If we just fiddle around at the surface of the Pandora's box which<br>
is nuclear energy, all these terrible things come out. We have to dig deeper to find the important hopes which it also carries.<br>
Using it as a warmaking device -which was the first application and the most noteworthy in history- is not allowable.<br>
Using that same application -atomic explosives- to explore the solar system, is disentangling nuclear power from the nightmare of the bomb.<br>
